---
import LegalLayout from '../components/legal/LegalLayout.astro';
import LegalSection from '../components/legal/LegalSection.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Draft License Terms | BMR PrintCare"
  description="Preliminary license terms placeholder for BMR PrintCare while the final software license and distribution model remain undecided."
  eyebrow="Draft license terms"
  heading="Preliminary license placeholder for future app distribution."
  intro="This page records the current license-term status without selecting a final desktop app license or distribution model."
  currentPath="/license-terms/"
>
  <LegalSection title="No final app license selected">
    <p>
      No final software license for the BMR PrintCare desktop app is selected in this website repository. This page is a
      preliminary placeholder and should not be treated as an open-source license, proprietary license, end-user license
      agreement, or commercial purchase agreement.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Repository and website status">
    <p>
      The website repository is marked private in its package metadata and does not include a dedicated license file at
      this stage. Future project owners should decide and document whether website code, app code, documentation, and
      brand assets have separate licensing rules.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Future desktop app distribution">
    <p>
      Before any desktop installer, binary, package, app store listing, or private beta build is distributed, the project
      should publish reviewed license terms that explain permitted use, restrictions, updates, support expectations,
      warranty limitations, and termination rules if applicable.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Third-party dependencies">
    <p>
      BMR PrintCare may rely on third-party dependencies for the website, desktop app, packaging, or documentation. Those
      dependencies can have their own licenses and notices. A future release should include a dependency notice process
      and any required attributions before distribution.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Commercial model not decided here">
    <p>
      This placeholder does not announce paid plans, subscriptions, purchases, commercial licensing, app store
      distribution, or public availability. Release status remains described on the <a href="/download/">release
      preparation page</a>, with broader sequencing on the <a href="/roadmap/">roadmap</a>.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>
</LegalLayout>
